    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on </span><span class=\"english\">“</span><span class=\"english\">Relationship</span><span class=\"english\">” </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences.                                           </span><span class=\"english\">10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Relationship</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A relationship is a connection between two or more people, and it can take many forms, such as friendships, romantic partnerships, or familial bonds. Relationships are built on trust, communication, and shared experiences. They can be sources of support, joy, and growth, but also challenges and conflicts. Healthy relationships are based on mutual respect and understanding, where both parties value each other's needs and feelings. Conflicts are natural in any relationship, but how they are handled determines the strength of the bond. Strong relationships require effort, compromise, and patience. They thrive when both individuals are </span><span class=\"english\">committed to nurturing the connection, whether through quality time or emotional support. Over time, relationships evolve and may require adaptation to meet the changing needs of both individuals involved. The value of a relationship is not just in its positive moments, but in how both people work through difficult times. In essence, relationships are essential to human life, which offers companionship, love, and a sense of belonging.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Relationship</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">---------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A relationship is a bond between two or more individuals, encompassing various forms like friendships, romantic relationships, or familial bonds.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Relationships: Trust, Communication, and Shared Experiences</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> (Any 6) -----06 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Relationships are built on trust, communication, and shared experiences.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• They provide support, joy, growth, and challenges.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Healthy relationships are based on mutual respect and understanding.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Conflicts are natural but handled with effort and patience.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Strong relationships thrive when both individuals are committed to nurturing the connection.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Relationships evolve over time, requiring adaptation to meet changing needs.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• The value of a relationship extends beyond positive moments to managing difficult times.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Relationships are fundamental to human life, providing companionship, love, and a sense of belonging.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">“Man is by nature a social animal.” </span><span class=\"english\">Explain this with reference to the context. </span><span><span> </span> </span><span class=\"english\">5</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">“Man is by nature a social animal,” is a famous quote uttered by the famous Greek philosopher Aristotle. </span><span class=\"english\">Humans are inherently social creatures. From early civilizations to modern societies, our ability to form and maintain social connections has been essential for survival, cooperation, and cultural development. Social interactions fulfil fundamental needs for companionship, cooperation, and emotional support, contributing significantly to our overall well-being. Through these interactions, we not only satisfy basic social needs but also shape our identities and sense of belonging within communities. </span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:                                                                              </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Identification of the Quote and Source </span><span class=\"english\">---------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Uttered by the famous Greek philosopher Aristotle from the lesson of Family Relationship.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Human Social Creativity and Social Connections</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">) ---</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Humans are inherently social creatures.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Social connections essential for survival, cooperation, and cultural development.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Social interactions fulfill companionship, cooperation, and emotional support needs.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Social interactions shape identities and sense of belonging.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">**For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Read the text below and fill in the gaps with the clues given in the box. There are more words than necessary. Make any grammatical changes (if necessary).</span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>                                 5</span></p><p><span><img src=\"images/Varsity_Kha_Weekly_Live_Exam-08_Set_2_f5f2fed8.png\"/></span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The speaker of the poem ‘Those Winter Sundays’ realizes from his adult (a)___</span><span class=\"english\">__</span><span class=\"english\"> that he took his father for (b)</span><span class=\"english\"> _____</span><span class=\"english\">. Now in adulthood, he more fully understands what it means to make sacrifices for others. Now, he can look back on his (c)</span><span class=\"english\"> _____</span><span class=\"english\"> and appreciate the way his father was carrying out his duties and responsibilities. Most children can't fully appreciate their parents because they (d)</span><span class=\"english\"> _____</span><span class=\"english\">to be responsible yet for another human being. \"Those Winter Sundays,\" then, has a kind of sadness to it that is equal parts nostalgic and (e)</span><span class=\"english\"> _____</span><span class=\"english\">. The speaker knows he can't travel back in time and show his gratitude to his father, but that he can at least record it in the poem.</span><span> </span></p>",
